'''Claudia Mitchell''' (born 1980) is the first woman to be outfitted with a [[bionic]] arm. She was outfitted with the arm to replace the arm she lost in a motorcycle accident.<ref>{{cite news | first = David | last = Brown | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/09/13/AR2006091302271.html?nav=E8 | title = For 1st Woman With Bionic Arm, a New Life Is Within Reach | publisher = The Washington Post | date = 2006-09-14 | accessdate = 2006-09-14 }}</ref>
Her prosthesis, a prototype developed by the [[Rehabilitation Institute of Chicago]] is one of the most advanced prosthetic arms developed to date.
