{{See also|Grand title of the Emperor of Austria}}
===Titles and styles===
* '''18 August 1830 – 2 December 1848''': ''His Imperial and Royal Highness'' Archduke and Prince Francis Joseph of Austria, Prince of Hungary, Bohemia and Croatia<ref name="harmonische Wahlkapitulation">{{cite book|title=Kaiser Joseph II. harmonische Wahlkapitulation mit allen den vorhergehenden Wahlkapitulationen der vorigen Kaiser und Könige}} Since 1780 official title used for princes ("''zu Ungarn, Böhmen, Dalmatien, Kroatien, Slawonien, Königlicher Erbprinz''")</ref>
* '''2 December 1848 – 21 November 1916''': ''His Imperial and Royal Apostolic Majesty'' The Emperor of Austria, Apostolic King of Hungary

His official grand title after the ''[[Ausgleich]]'' of 1867 was: "Francis Joseph the First, by the Grace of God [[Emperor of Austria]], Apostolic King of [[Hungary]], King of [[Kingdom of Bohemia|Bohemia]], King of [[Kingdom of Dalmatia|Dalmatia]], [[Kingdom of Croatia-Slavonia|Croatia]], [[Kingdom of Slavonia|Slavonia]], [[Kingdom of Galicia and Lodomeria|Galicia and Lodomeria]] and [[Kingdom of Illyria (1816–49)|Illyria]]; King of [[Kingdom of Jerusalem|Jerusalem]] etc., Archduke of [[Archduchy of Austria|Austria]]; Grand Duke of [[Grand Duchy of Tuscany|Tuscany]] and [[Grand Duchy of Cracow|Cracow]], Duke of [[Duchy of Lorraine|Lorraine]], of [[Duchy of Salzburg|Salzburg]], [[Duchy of Styria|Styria]], [[Duchy of Carinthia|Carinthia]], [[Duchy of Carniola|Carniola]] and of [[Duchy of Bukovina|Bukovina]]; Grand Prince of [[Grand Principality of Transylvania|Transylvania]]; Margrave of [[Margraviate of Moravia|Moravia]]; Duke of [[Austrian Silesia|Upper and Lower Silesia]], of [[Duchy of Modena|Modena]], [[Duchy of Parma|Parma]], [[Duchy of Piacenza|Piacenza]] and [[Duchy of Guastalla|Guastalla]], of [[Duchy of Oświęcim|Oświęcim]], [[Duchy of Zator|Zator]] and [[Duchy of Teschen|Ćeszyn]], [[Duchy of Friuli|Friuli]], Ragusa ([[Dubrovnik]]) and Zara ([[Zadar]]); Princely Count of [[Habsburg]] and [[County of Tyrol|Tyrol]], of [[County of Kyburg|Kyburg]], [[County of Gorizia and Gradisca|Gorizia and Gradisca]]; Prince of Trent (Trento) and Brixen; Margrave of [[Upper Lusatia|Upper]] and [[Lower Lusatia|Lower]] [[Lusatia]] and in [[Margraviate of Istria|Istria]]; Count of [[County of Hohenems|Hohenems]], [[County of Feldkirch|Feldkirch]], [[County of Bregenz|Bregenz]], [[County of Sonnenberg|Sonnenberg]], etc.; Lord of Trieste, of Cattaro (Kotor), and over the [[Windic march]]; [[Grosswojwod|Grand Voivode]] of the [[Voivodeship of Serbia and Banat of Temeschwar|Voivodship of Serbia]]."<ref>The official title of the ruler of Austrian Empire and later the Austria-Hungary had been changed several times: by a patent from 1 August 1804, by a court office decree from 22 August 1836, by an imperial court ministry decree from 6 January 1867 and finally by a letter from 12 December 1867. Shorter versions were recommended for official documents and international treaties: "Emperor of Austria, King of Bohemia etc. and Apostolic King of Hungary", "Emperor of Austria and Apostolic King of Hungary", "His Majesty The Emperor and King" and "His Imperial and Royal Apostolic Majesty". The term ''[[Kaiserlich und königlich]]'' (''K.u.K.'') was decreed in a letter from 17 October 1889 for the military, the navy and the institutions shared by both parts of the monarchy.<br />From the [[Otto's encyclopedia]] (published during 1888–1909), subject 'King', [http://encyklopedie.seznam.cz/heslo/285233-kral online in Czech].</ref>

===Honours===
{{refimprove|section|date=November 2017}}<!--most entries are not cited-->
====National====
* He was Grand Master of the following chivalric orders:<ref name="p5">Justus Perthes, ''Almanach de Gotha 1916'' (1916) [https://archive.org/details/almanachdegotha01unse_0/page/n63 page 5]</ref>
** [[Order of the Golden Fleece#Austrian_Order|Order of the Golden Fleece]]<br>(''Orden vom Goldenen Vlies'', ex officio as Emperor of Austria)
** [[Military Order of Maria Theresa]]<br>(''Militär Maria-Theresien-Orden'', ex officio as Emperor of Austria)
** [[Order of Saint Stephen of Hungary|Royal Hungarian Order of Saint Stephen]]<br>(''Königlich ungarischer St. Stephan-Orden'', ex officio as Emperor of Austria)
** [[Order of Leopold (Austria)|Austrian Imperial Order of Leopold ]]<br>(''Leopold-Orden'', ex officio as Emperor of Austria)
** [[Order of the Iron Crown (Austria)| Imperial Order of the Iron Crown]]<br>(''Orden der Eisernen Krone'', ex officio as Emperor of Austria)
* Austrian War Medal
* Cross of Honour for 50 years of military service
* Military Cross for the 60th year of the reign

In addition, he founded the [[Order of Franz Joseph]] (''Franz Joseph-Orden'') in 1849, and the [[Order of Elizabeth]] (''Elizabeth-Orden'') in 1898.

