{{artist-stub}}

'''Kenneth Samuel Kleinknecht''' (July 24, 1919 – November 20, 2007) worked for the [[National Advisory Committee on Aeronautics]] as an engineer and continued at [[NASA]] to become a manager of the [[Project Mercury|Mercury]], [[Project Gemini|Gemini]], [[Apollo Command/Service Module|Apollo CSM]], [[Skylab]], [[Space Shuttle program|Shuttle]], and [[Spacelab]]. After retiring from NASA, he worked for [[Lockheed Martin]] for 9 years.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.jsc.nasa.gov/history/oral_histories/KleinknechtKS/KSK_BIO.pdf |title=NASA Johnson Space Center Oral History Project Biographical Data Sheet for Kenny Kleinknecht |access-date=2018-08-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/140847331/kenneth-s.-kleinknecht/photo |title=Kenneth S. Kleinknecht (1919-2007) |website=www.findagrave.com |access-date=2018-08-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.collectspace.com/ubb/Forum38/HTML/000736.html |title=Mercury manager Kenny Kleinknecht (1919-2007) |date=2007-11-22 |website=www.collectspace.com |access-date=2018-08-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.legacy.com/obituaries/denverpost/obituary.aspx?n=kenneth-s-kleinknecht&pid=98530758 |title=Kenneth S. Kleinknecht |date=2007-11-25}}</ref>
